CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER - RUSSIA (VOLGOGRAD)
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Tue 3 Apr 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News Agency "Ural Business Consulting" [trans. Assoc.Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.urbc.ru/newnews.asp?ida=155885>

An outbreak of classical swine fever [CSF] has been recorded in the
Volgograd region. The press-service of Volgograd's Emergency
Situations Ministry reported that 51 pigs [have died between] 26 Mar
2007 and today [3 Apr 2007] in a private farm in Gorodishche [see map
at
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RS/84/Gorodishche.html>.]
The investigations, carried out in the All-Russia Scientific Research
Institute of Veterinary Virology and Microbiology (Pokrov, Moscow
region), confirmed the diagnosis of classical swine fever.
Classical swine fever does not challenge public health. All dead
animals were incinerated in a specially allocated installation.
Quarantine has been imposed in the affected farmstead. Vaccination of
offspring and additional precautionary measures have been undertaken.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The outbreak described, reportedly confirmed by a national
laboratory, is Russia's 2nd CSF outbreak this year [2007]. On 22 Feb
2007, Russia notified the OIE (World Animal Health Organization)
about the reoccurrence of CSF in Starominskaya, Starominsk,
Krasnodarskiy Kray. See map at
<http://www.multimap.com/map//map/browse.cgi?lat=46.5246&lon=39.0554&scale=2000000&icon=x>,
and the notification in OIE Disease Information, WAHID [World Animal
Health Information Database], weekly disease information Vol.20,
No.9, 28 Feb 2007, at
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>.
A list of countries by their CSF disease situation, including the 7
sections "Never occurred," "absent during the report period,"
"current unresolved disease events," "disease suspected," "infection
present (with no clinical disease," "demonstrated clinical disease,"
and "disease restricted to certain zone(s)/region(s) of the country"
can be found in OIE's WAHID interface, at
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=disease_status_lists>.
At present, the following 10 countries are included in the list
"current unresolved disease events":
Country / Start date / Reason for notification
Bolivia / 25 Aug 2006 / Reoccurrence
Brazil / 5 Jan 2007 / Reoccurrence
Bulgaria / 3 Feb 2006 / Reoccurrence
Croatia / 17 Jul 2006 / Reoccurrence
Ecuador / 16 Oct 2006 / Reoccurrence
Germany / 1 Mar 2006 / Reoccurrence
Guatemala / 20 Apr 2006 / Reoccurrence
Hungary / 10 Jan 2007 / Reoccurrence
Nicaragua / 12 Dec 2006 / Reoccurrence
Russia / 17 Feb 2007 / Reoccurrence
The current outbreak, hundreds of kilometers east to the outbreak in
Krasnodar, is expected to be notified to the OIE with complementary
data. - Mod.AS]
